Interface Remote

  • All Superinterfaces:

    All Known Implementing Classes:

    public interface Remote
extends java.io.Serializable
    The Remote interface serves to identify interfaces whose methods may be invoked from a non-local virtual machine. Any object that is a remote object must directly or indirectly implement this interface. Only those methods specified in a "remote interface", an interface that extends omq.Remote are available remotely.
    Author:
    Sergi Toda
